unittitle_ssm: Records of the Gallatin Arts Festival
abstract_ssm: The Gallatin Arts Festival (GAF) is a week-long community-wide celebration of art and the interdisciplinary scholarship of students within New York University's Gallatin School. The festival features student work in the visual and performing arts. The Records of the Gallatin Arts Festival (1987-1993) include promotional materials, newspaper clippings, photographs, budgets, meeting minutes, event programs, NYU publications, performer biographies, questionnaires, and calendars.
